From: Seth Chou <scss1199@gmail.com>
Subject: [PATCH] fix(teacache): accept video_coords kwarg in teacache_ltx_forward
Target: SD.Next commit 0eb4a98e0 (2026-04-04) or later
File: modules/teacache/teacache_ltx.py

`modules/teacache/teacache_ltx.py::teacache_ltx_forward` is monkey-patched
onto `LTXVideoTransformer3DModel.forward` at video model load time (see
`modules/video_models/video_cache.py:apply_teacache_patch`). Its signature
was written against an older diffusers `LTXVideoTransformer3DModel.forward`
and missed the `video_coords` keyword argument that diffusers now passes
when running `LTXConditionPipeline` in image-conditioning (I2V) mode.

Symptom: with `Settings -> Transformers cache enabled` ON, every LTX I2V
generation crashes at the first transformer step:

    TypeError: teacache_ltx_forward() got an unexpected keyword argument
    'video_coords'

Reproducer:
- Tab "Video", Engine "LTX Video", Model "LTXVideo 0.9.6 2B I2V"
- Settings -> teacache_enabled = True (default for LTX in many configs)
- Provide an init image and click Generate

Fix: accept `video_coords` and forward it to `self.rope(...)`. Diffusers'
`LTXVideoRotaryPosEmbed` already handles the `(rope_interpolation_scale,
video_coords)` pair correctly — `video_coords is not None` selects the
image-conditioning branch.

Workaround without this patch: disable Transformers cache (Settings ->
teacache_enabled = False) and restart SD.Next so the monkey-patch is
re-evaluated against the new opts.

Discovered: 2026-04-25 on Intel Arc A770 16GB + LTX-Video 0.9.6 2B I2V,
locally-cached weights (Lightricks/LTX-Video repo).

---
diff --git a/modules/teacache/teacache_ltx.py b/modules/teacache/teacache_ltx.py
index 23d4897c0..16e510ede 100644
--- a/modules/teacache/teacache_ltx.py
+++ b/modules/teacache/teacache_ltx.py
@@ -18,6 +18,7 @@ def teacache_ltx_forward(
         height: int,
         width: int,
         rope_interpolation_scale: Optional[Tuple[float, float, float]] = None,
+        video_coords: Optional[torch.Tensor] = None,
         attention_kwargs: Optional[Dict[str, Any]] = None,
         return_dict: bool = True,
     ) -> torch.Tensor:
@@ -36,7 +37,7 @@ def teacache_ltx_forward(
                 "Passing `scale` via `attention_kwargs` when not using the PEFT backend is ineffective."
             )

-    image_rotary_emb = self.rope(hidden_states, num_frames, height, width, rope_interpolation_scale)
+    image_rotary_emb = self.rope(hidden_states, num_frames, height, width, rope_interpolation_scale, video_coords)

     # convert encoder_attention_mask to a bias the same way we do for attention_mask
     if encoder_attention_mask is not None and encoder_attention_mask.ndim == 2:
